# Security and Compliance Rules

- Never log PHI.
- Never put secrets in code.
- Never put secrets in client-exposed environment variables.
- Never use real patient data in examples, tests, prompts, screenshots, or fixtures.
- Use synthetic/fake data only.
- Every tenant-sensitive query must include organization and applicable clinic/team/bucket scope.
- Cross-clinic data leakage is a critical incident.
- Sensitive actions require audit logs.
- Webhooks require authentication or signature verification.
- Webhooks require idempotency.
- Patient search must use PHI-safe encrypted/hash/token search patterns.
- Do not build broad decrypted PHI search.
- Do not create fake compliance claims.

Access must support isolation by:

- organization
- pharmacy site
- clinic/practice account
- team
- user
- role
- permission
- bucket
- workstation
